Qed.

Theorem (maximumislocalmaximum):
  for all v0, (if v0 is a real number then for all v1, (if v1 is an open neighbourhood of v0 and v1 is an interval then for all v2, (if v2 is a map from \mathbb{R} to \mathbb{R} then (if v0 is a maximum of v2 on v1 then v0 is a local maximum of v2))))
Proof:
  \delta is a real number and \delta is positive and \B_{ \delta }( \xi ) is a subclass of E
  \delta is a maximum domain restrictor for f around \xi
Qed.

